1
00:00:06,065 --> 00:00:08,585
I'll do whatever it takes
to win your heart.

2
00:00:08,665 --> 00:00:10,505
<i>And I've already started.</i>

3
00:00:10,585 --> 00:00:12,345
<i>Does that make me special enough?</i>

4
00:00:15,345 --> 00:00:17,465
Could you stay with me for a while?

5
00:00:18,065 --> 00:00:19,625
<i>Withdraw from this project.</i>

6
00:00:19,705 --> 00:00:22,585
<i>How do you think people</i>
<i>in this company will see Piang,</i>

7
00:00:22,665 --> 00:00:23,505
<i>when the chairwoman's granddaughter</i>

8
00:00:23,585 --> 00:00:26,345
<i>is chasing after</i>
<i>a food researcher like this?</i>

9
00:00:26,425 --> 00:00:28,185
I owe everyone an apology.

10
00:00:28,265 --> 00:00:30,785
<i>I won't be able to present this project.</i>

11
00:00:30,865 --> 00:00:32,785
What happened? Why all of a sudden--

12
00:00:32,864 --> 00:00:34,425
Just leave me alone.

13
00:00:49,465 --> 00:00:50,825
Song, wait.

14
00:00:51,345 --> 00:00:54,305
-What happened? Why all of a sudden--
-Just leave me alone.

15
00:01:12,465 --> 00:01:13,545
Hey, Sis.

16
00:01:13,625 --> 00:01:14,905
-Stop--
-What happened, Song?

17
00:01:14,985 --> 00:01:17,905
Before the meeting,
Ploy already had you recheck the data.

18
00:01:17,985 --> 00:01:21,025
If the formula was really wrong
like you said, you would've told us.

19
00:01:21,105 --> 00:01:22,425
Sis, calm down.

20
00:01:22,505 --> 00:01:23,785
How can I calm down?

21
00:01:28,985 --> 00:01:31,185
-I'm sorry--
-I don't want an apology.

22
00:01:31,265 --> 00:01:33,385
I want the truth.

23
00:01:34,785 --> 00:01:36,185
I won't calm down.

24
00:01:36,265 --> 00:01:37,505
The reason I'm so angry,

25
00:01:37,585 --> 00:01:39,025
is not because you ruined it.

26
00:01:39,105 --> 00:01:43,105
It's because you always
keep everything to yourself.

27
00:01:43,185 --> 00:01:44,865
We're on the same team.

28
00:01:44,945 --> 00:01:46,665
We're practically family already.

29
00:01:47,185 --> 00:01:49,745
So why don't you trust us even now?

30
00:02:04,905 --> 00:02:08,065
Sarut told me
to withdraw from this project.

31
00:02:09,465 --> 00:02:12,385
If I don't, Piang will get dragged
into this mess.

32
00:02:15,625 --> 00:02:17,105
What does Piang have to do with it?

33
00:02:18,145 --> 00:02:20,465
He found out about me and Piang.

34
00:02:21,105 --> 00:02:24,145
He even threatened to tell everyone.

35
00:02:24,665 --> 00:02:27,705
If it were just me, I wouldn't be afraid.

36
00:02:28,905 --> 00:02:31,225
But Piang is involved.

37
00:02:33,185 --> 00:02:34,425
I'm worried about her.

38
00:02:36,265 --> 00:02:38,385
He actually went that far?

39
00:02:38,465 --> 00:02:40,385
He said he has evidence.

40
00:02:41,305 --> 00:02:43,545
He's probably
been collecting it for a while.

41
00:02:43,625 --> 00:02:45,065
Both photos and videos.

42
00:02:45,145 --> 00:02:46,225
Honestly,

43
00:02:46,305 --> 00:02:48,425
I always knew that bastard

44
00:02:48,505 --> 00:02:49,745
would try to get back at you.

45
00:02:49,825 --> 00:02:52,105
You took the Best Researcher
title from him.

46
00:02:52,185 --> 00:02:55,265
But honestly,
I didn't think he'd stoop this low.

47
00:02:55,345 --> 00:02:57,025
He's capable of anything, Sis.

48
00:02:57,105 --> 00:02:58,185
I used to work under him.

49
00:02:58,265 --> 00:02:59,865
I know exactly what he's capable of.

50
00:03:01,185 --> 00:03:04,065
That's why I said
I'm so lucky to be with all of you.

51
00:03:11,225 --> 00:03:14,665
I owe you both an apology,
Nampraw and Ploy.

52
00:03:15,945 --> 00:03:17,705
I'm sorry things turned out like this.

53
00:03:23,505 --> 00:03:24,465
It's okay.

54
00:03:24,985 --> 00:03:26,385
We understand now.

55
00:03:27,025 --> 00:03:28,825
Just stay strong.

56
00:03:29,665 --> 00:03:31,105
We're on the same team.

57
00:04:57,145 --> 00:04:58,825
Were you eavesdropping on us?

58
00:05:01,985 --> 00:05:03,065
Yes.

59
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:05,225
And I heard everything.

60
00:05:05,825 --> 00:05:08,065
Song, I'll handle this myself.

61
00:05:08,145 --> 00:05:09,985
How are you going to do that?

62
00:05:10,065 --> 00:05:13,505
I'll tell everyone myself
that I'm the one chasing you.

63
00:05:13,585 --> 00:05:14,425
There will be nothing
for anyone to expose.

64
00:05:14,505 --> 00:05:16,905
But you're the chairwoman's granddaughter.

65
00:05:16,985 --> 00:05:18,585
-Don't you feel ashamed--
-No.

66
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:23,305
What's truly pathetic
is letting someone you love suffer

67
00:05:23,385 --> 00:05:24,545
and doing nothing about it.

68
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:26,465
Piang, don't.

69
00:05:29,185 --> 00:05:31,585
That'll only make things worse.

70
00:05:31,665 --> 00:05:33,825
Then how do we fix this?

71
00:05:33,905 --> 00:05:38,345
It's not fair that your team
has to lose because of his dirty tricks.

72
00:05:41,785 --> 00:05:43,305
Like I said,

73
00:05:43,825 --> 00:05:47,945
the best solution
is for you to stay away from me.

74
00:05:48,025 --> 00:05:49,705
-But that's not--
-It's not that hard.

75
00:05:51,625 --> 00:05:53,585
Just stop pursuing me

76
00:05:54,305 --> 00:05:56,985
and spend your time
with someone more suitable.

77
00:06:03,425 --> 00:06:04,985
Who do you mean by that?

78
00:06:07,905 --> 00:06:09,625
The one your grandmother picked for you.

79
00:06:13,945 --> 00:06:15,145
Trust me.

80
00:06:16,265 --> 00:06:18,865
It's the only way to end this.

81
00:06:20,465 --> 00:06:22,265
If you really like me,

82
00:06:23,505 --> 00:06:25,385
then consider this my request.

83
00:06:26,585 --> 00:06:28,145
Please do this for me.

84
00:07:28,745 --> 00:07:29,705
Excuse me.

85
00:07:31,985 --> 00:07:35,345
Mudmee asked me to invite
both of you to her office.

86
00:07:36,225 --> 00:07:37,265
Yes.

87
00:07:46,025 --> 00:07:48,105
I have an announcement.

88
00:07:48,825 --> 00:07:52,105
Since you two are currently tied

89
00:07:52,185 --> 00:07:54,345
and have the highest scores,

90
00:07:54,425 --> 00:07:56,425
management and I have agreed

91
00:07:56,505 --> 00:07:59,105
to hold an official competition

92
00:07:59,185 --> 00:08:02,305
to determine this year's
Mega Excellent winner.

93
00:08:02,385 --> 00:08:05,545
I'll announce the challenge
and rules as soon as possible.

94
00:08:09,105 --> 00:08:10,145
I have a question.

95
00:08:11,705 --> 00:08:15,665
If one team is unable to participate,

96
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:18,105
does the other team automatically win?

97
00:08:19,545 --> 00:08:20,545
No.

98
00:08:22,385 --> 00:08:24,385
For this competition,

99
00:08:24,465 --> 00:08:27,985
withdrawal will not be allowed,
regardless of the reason.

100
00:08:55,065 --> 00:08:57,825
Your grandmother is sitting right here.
Don't you see her?

101
00:08:57,905 --> 00:08:59,505
Come talk to me first.

102
00:09:02,225 --> 00:09:04,025
Yes, Grandma.

103
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:07,665
How did your date with Dr. Namking go?

104
00:09:08,185 --> 00:09:09,785
Why are you back so early?

105
00:09:09,865 --> 00:09:12,185
I waited there for an hour,

106
00:09:12,265 --> 00:09:13,745
but she never showed up.

107
00:09:14,745 --> 00:09:17,625
Is this really the person you said
was perfect for me?

108
00:09:19,305 --> 00:09:20,785
I'll excuse myself.

109
00:09:40,425 --> 00:09:44,945
I'd like to thank everyone
for supporting our foundation.

110
00:09:45,025 --> 00:09:47,185
Now, please excuse me
while I call the director.

111
00:09:47,265 --> 00:09:49,065
Please enjoy yourselves.

112
00:09:49,145 --> 00:09:49,985
Please do.

113
00:09:56,745 --> 00:10:01,345
Ms. Pannee’s foundation
that tackles violence

114
00:10:01,425 --> 00:10:04,345
has received tremendous support.

115
00:10:04,425 --> 00:10:05,865
I hope that

116
00:10:05,945 --> 00:10:08,585
the stray dog and cat rescue foundation

117
00:10:08,665 --> 00:10:12,465
I'm working on
will receive the same support.

118
00:10:14,425 --> 00:10:18,145
I'll have to think carefully

119
00:10:18,225 --> 00:10:19,945
about whether I'll support it.

120
00:10:20,025 --> 00:10:22,825
I've already apologized
on my granddaughter's behalf

121
00:10:22,905 --> 00:10:25,025
for making Piang wait.

122
00:10:25,105 --> 00:10:26,705
And not showing up as promised.

123
00:10:27,545 --> 00:10:28,625
For a doctor,

124
00:10:28,705 --> 00:10:32,505
a patient's life comes first.

125
00:10:34,345 --> 00:10:38,105
That proves if they get married someday,

126
00:10:38,625 --> 00:10:41,625
she'll take excellent care of her partner.

127
00:10:51,185 --> 00:10:52,705
You do have a point.

128
00:10:54,225 --> 00:10:55,305
Fine.

129
00:10:55,385 --> 00:10:58,345
I'll give her one more chance.

130
00:10:58,425 --> 00:11:03,905
I figure no one suits Piang better
than your granddaughter.

131
00:11:06,505 --> 00:11:08,825
But don't let her mess up again.

132
00:11:08,905 --> 00:11:10,105
Otherwise,

133
00:11:10,185 --> 00:11:13,345
I won't help your foundation.

134
00:11:21,105 --> 00:11:22,065
Excuse me.

135
00:11:23,505 --> 00:11:26,065
Are you laughing at me?

136
00:11:26,785 --> 00:11:31,385
Sorry to say, but yes, I am.

137
00:11:33,025 --> 00:11:35,465
What's so funny?

138
00:11:36,225 --> 00:11:38,705
What you were just talking about.

139
00:11:38,785 --> 00:11:40,305
Honestly,

140
00:11:40,385 --> 00:11:44,985
I wasn't trying
to pry into anyone's business.

141
00:11:45,065 --> 00:11:47,985
But you were speaking so loudly

142
00:11:48,065 --> 00:11:50,185
that I couldn't help but overhear.

143
00:11:50,265 --> 00:11:52,025
And the reason I laughed

144
00:11:52,105 --> 00:11:54,585
is because of the way you think.

145
00:11:54,665 --> 00:11:59,945
You see your granddaughter
as a business tool.

146
00:12:00,025 --> 00:12:03,265
You set her up for your own benefit.

147
00:12:03,345 --> 00:12:06,105
I honestly didn't realize

148
00:12:06,185 --> 00:12:08,505
people still think like that these days.

149
00:12:08,585 --> 00:12:12,025
So when I heard it,
it was just ridiculous.

150
00:12:12,105 --> 00:12:13,585
I couldn't help laughing.

151
00:12:18,225 --> 00:12:19,865
I'll get going now.

152
00:12:27,425 --> 00:12:30,385
Hey, who is that woman?

153
00:12:30,465 --> 00:12:32,785
How dare she talk to me like that?

154
00:12:33,305 --> 00:12:34,545
Why wouldn't she?

155
00:12:34,625 --> 00:12:38,545
She's M.R. Salika Warakijaruwongs.

156
00:12:39,505 --> 00:12:42,145
Rich, and of royal descent.

157
00:12:42,225 --> 00:12:43,385
She's sharp-tongued.

158
00:12:43,905 --> 00:12:45,425
She's usually very private.

159
00:12:45,505 --> 00:12:47,185
She rarely attends events like this.

160
00:12:48,585 --> 00:12:52,585
This is probably her first one in years.

161
00:14:53,385 --> 00:14:56,985
MON

162
00:15:06,145 --> 00:15:08,225
Hello. Are you free?

163
00:15:08,305 --> 00:15:09,505
Come see me at the office.

164
00:15:10,345 --> 00:15:13,065
I am. But I'm not coming.

165
00:15:13,985 --> 00:15:15,705
My heart is broken.

166
00:15:15,785 --> 00:15:18,025
<i>I don't have the energy to go anywhere.</i>

167
00:15:18,105 --> 00:15:20,585
What? Did you and Song have a fight?

168
00:15:23,145 --> 00:15:26,185
Then I guess you don't want to see
Song's feature that airs tomorrow.

169
00:15:26,265 --> 00:15:27,985
<i>What a shame.</i>

170
00:15:28,065 --> 00:15:30,065
<i>I wanted you to be the first to see it.</i>

171
00:15:30,145 --> 00:15:31,385
Wait.

172
00:15:31,465 --> 00:15:32,785
I'm on my way.

173
00:15:37,065 --> 00:15:38,625
<i>Someone mature.</i>

174
00:15:38,705 --> 00:15:39,745
<i>Age doesn't matter.</i>

175
00:15:39,825 --> 00:15:41,225
<i>It's about their mindset and character.</i>

176
00:15:41,305 --> 00:15:42,745
<i>They should be well-presented</i>

177
00:15:42,825 --> 00:15:45,025
<i>in both appearance and personality.</i>

178
00:15:45,545 --> 00:15:48,185
<i>Someone who gets it right away,</i>
<i>isn't childish…</i>

179
00:15:48,265 --> 00:15:49,465
Piang.

180
00:15:49,545 --> 00:15:51,225
How much longer are you
going to keep quiet?

181
00:15:54,985 --> 00:15:57,585
I don't know how I'm supposed to feel.

182
00:15:58,305 --> 00:16:01,705
Part of me is happy seeing her shine,

183
00:16:01,785 --> 00:16:04,185
but another part is sad

184
00:16:05,025 --> 00:16:06,825
that I'm not there with her.

185
00:16:07,745 --> 00:16:11,505
Looking into her eyes, holding her hand,
and admiring her.

186
00:16:14,585 --> 00:16:15,865
Piangrawin.

187
00:16:15,945 --> 00:16:19,105
Why is your life so tragic?

188
00:16:20,945 --> 00:16:22,225
Hey.

189
00:16:23,625 --> 00:16:25,105
You don't need to comfort me.

190
00:16:25,185 --> 00:16:26,585
I'm not comforting you.

191
00:16:26,665 --> 00:16:29,545
I'm telling you to move
your face away from my screen.

192
00:16:29,625 --> 00:16:31,625
This screen is expensive. You'll break it.

193
00:16:37,425 --> 00:16:38,785
Thanks a lot, friend.

194
00:16:42,505 --> 00:16:43,945
Honestly,

195
00:16:45,105 --> 00:16:47,385
if Song wasn't being threatened,

196
00:16:48,425 --> 00:16:50,425
would she really want you out of her life?

197
00:16:51,305 --> 00:16:53,945
No. I'm sure of it.

198
00:16:54,025 --> 00:16:56,345
I believe Song feels something for me too.

199
00:16:57,065 --> 00:16:59,945
There have been so many times
when she let it show.

200
00:17:01,105 --> 00:17:03,065
Especially,

201
00:17:05,184 --> 00:17:06,585
when we slept together.

202
00:17:07,825 --> 00:17:09,145
Slept together?

203
00:17:15,545 --> 00:17:16,985
Then if you want to see her,

204
00:17:17,065 --> 00:17:18,424
there is a way.

205
00:17:20,464 --> 00:17:21,305
How so?

206
00:17:21,385 --> 00:17:23,545
Friends with benefits.

207
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:27,224
A relationship where two people meet
just to sleep together.

208
00:17:27,305 --> 00:17:29,745
So why don't you suggest that to her?

209
00:17:30,265 --> 00:17:32,545
But you'll have to make her believe

210
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:35,345
that's all you really want from her.

211
00:17:35,425 --> 00:17:37,265
No strings attached.

212
00:17:38,265 --> 00:17:42,465
But friends with benefits
isn't supposed to involve feelings, right?

213
00:17:42,545 --> 00:17:43,265
Yes.

214
00:17:43,345 --> 00:17:45,305
But you said it yourself.

215
00:17:45,385 --> 00:17:48,185
You're sure she already
has feelings for you.

216
00:17:49,105 --> 00:17:50,985
And if that's true,

217
00:17:51,065 --> 00:17:54,385
asking her to be friends with benefits

218
00:17:54,465 --> 00:17:57,825
will only make her fall for you even more.

219
00:18:04,785 --> 00:18:07,585
You're a genius, my friend.

220
00:18:07,665 --> 00:18:08,905
Obviously.

221
00:18:10,905 --> 00:18:14,145
Then why did you try to stop me from
having a one-night stand with Song?

222
00:18:14,225 --> 00:18:17,545
What happened?
Did your nun spirit leave your body?

223
00:18:17,625 --> 00:18:18,585
No.

224
00:18:19,825 --> 00:18:23,145
I just didn't want to see you like this.

225
00:18:25,265 --> 00:18:27,305
You looked like a dying puppy.

226
00:18:28,185 --> 00:18:29,185
Aw.

227
00:18:29,265 --> 00:18:31,865
-So pitiful.
-Hey.

228
00:18:33,105 --> 00:18:35,105
Am I a dog again?

229
00:18:35,185 --> 00:18:36,065
Let me see your paw.

230
00:18:39,385 --> 00:18:40,665
Come here.

231
00:18:40,745 --> 00:18:42,425
Leave me alone.

232
00:18:42,505 --> 00:18:44,665
-Come here.
-No.

233
00:18:44,745 --> 00:18:45,865
It's perfect.

234
00:18:58,905 --> 00:18:59,705
1. USE FOOD TECH OR CHEMISTRY.

235
00:18:59,785 --> 00:19:00,625
2. CONNECT TASTE, AROMA,
AND TEXTURE TO LOVE.

236
00:19:00,705 --> 00:19:02,025
3. MAIN INGREDIENT
MUST FIT THE THEME'S STORY.

237
00:19:02,105 --> 00:19:03,665
4. NO WITHDRAWAL ALLOWED.

238
00:19:03,745 --> 00:19:05,865
TO COMPETE FOR THE MEGA EXCELLENT AWARD.

239
00:19:12,625 --> 00:19:14,785
You've seen the competition brief, right?

240
00:19:17,025 --> 00:19:20,425
"A dish that tastes like love."

241
00:19:23,265 --> 00:19:24,945
You must be thinking of Piang.

242
00:19:31,745 --> 00:19:34,265
You can stop using Piang to threaten me.

243
00:19:34,345 --> 00:19:35,665
It won't work anymore.

244
00:19:36,745 --> 00:19:37,945
Can't you see?

245
00:19:38,025 --> 00:19:40,625
The rules require both of us to compete.

246
00:19:40,705 --> 00:19:42,345
And neither of us can withdraw.

247
00:19:43,425 --> 00:19:44,465
True.

248
00:19:44,985 --> 00:19:48,505
I'm starting to wonder
what the boss is really after.

249
00:19:48,585 --> 00:19:51,105
Why is she so determined
to make us compete?

250
00:19:51,185 --> 00:19:54,145
Honestly, if she wanted you to win,

251
00:19:54,665 --> 00:19:55,625
she could just do that.

252
00:19:55,705 --> 00:19:56,545
After all, she…

253
00:20:01,425 --> 00:20:03,065
seems crazy about you.

254
00:20:04,585 --> 00:20:05,625
Or maybe…

255
00:20:06,665 --> 00:20:08,385
before you went after Piang,

256
00:20:09,425 --> 00:20:12,385
-you went after the boss first.
-Sarut.

257
00:20:13,705 --> 00:20:15,505
You're actually a very capable person.

258
00:20:16,105 --> 00:20:18,025
And you've got decades
more experience than I do.

259
00:20:18,745 --> 00:20:21,625
If you truly competed against me on merit,

260
00:20:22,145 --> 00:20:24,305
I'm sure beating me would be easy.

261
00:20:25,105 --> 00:20:28,945
You don't need dirty tricks
or a dirty mind like this.

262
00:20:29,465 --> 00:20:33,065
Well, maybe it's because
I've seen so much in life.

263
00:20:33,145 --> 00:20:34,425
That's why I know

264
00:20:34,505 --> 00:20:37,425
being the bad guy makes life easier.

265
00:20:37,505 --> 00:20:39,825
Then can I borrow that idea too?

266
